00:00:00.380 --> 00:00:05.490
Welcome to Buyspares.
This video will show you how to change the door catch on a

00:00:05.490 --> 00:00:09.570
washing machine.

00:00:09.570 --> 00:00:12.450
Before replacing a part in any
electrical appliance

00:00:12.450 --> 00:00:18.750
you must ensure that the appliance is first unplugged from the mains.

00:00:18.750 --> 00:00:22.570
Using a screwdriver remove the screws which attach the door to the body

00:00:22.570 --> 00:00:23.349
of the washing machine

00:00:23.349 --> 00:00:30.349
and set them aside to be replaced later.

00:00:35.380 --> 00:00:41.170
Remove the door and place it on a work
surface with the bowl facing upwards

00:00:41.170 --> 00:00:48.170
remove the five screws around the frame of the door
and set these aside as well.

00:01:00.150 --> 00:01:02.240
Separate the two halves of the door

00:01:02.240 --> 00:01:09.240
you might find a flat-screwdriver handy for doing this.

00:01:09.240 --> 00:01:16.240
Remove the metal hinge and the bowl and set these aside

00:01:22.359 --> 00:01:25.630
Please bear in mind that the method of
removing the catch may vary according

00:01:25.630 --> 00:01:26.500
to your brand of

00:01:26.500 --> 00:01:31.760
washing machine.

00:01:31.760 --> 00:01:35.620
Remove the screw the holds on the door
catch pin, notice that there is only one

00:01:35.620 --> 00:01:40.600
screw here.

00:01:40.600 --> 00:01:45.150
Remove the door catch and replace it with the
new one.

00:01:45.150 --> 00:01:52.150
Notice that this new catch is made of metal
to ensure a longer life.

00:01:52.920 --> 00:01:56.130
Replace the screw to fix on the door catch and tighten it with the

00:01:56.130 --> 00:02:03.130
screwdriver.

00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:14.260
Replace the bowl.

00:02:15.319 --> 00:02:22.319
Replace the hinge and all its components.

00:02:29.040 --> 00:02:36.040
And then replace the back half of the door
frame.

00:02:52.900 --> 00:02:59.900
Replace the five screws which go around
the door frame.

00:03:32.060 --> 00:03:35.430
Fix the door security back onto the
washing machine by replacing and

00:03:35.430 --> 00:03:42.430
tightening the screws.

00:03:57.910 --> 00:04:01.930
The washing machine is now ready to be plugged in and used.

00:04:01.930 --> 00:04:05.530
For all the parts you need visit

00:04:05.530 --> 00:04:07.830
www.buyspares.co.uk

